Running City Desk

   C‚i‚t‚y‚ ‚D‚e‚s‚k‚ may be loaded to run in two ways: from the CLI or from Workbench. This manual describes the latter method only. After loading Kickstart, the Amiga will prompt you to enter the Workbench disk. At this point insert C‚i‚t‚y‚ ‚D‚e‚s‚k‚ in the internal drive instead of the Workbench disk.
   Point to the C‚i‚t‚y‚ ‚D‚e‚s‚k‚ icon and double click the left mouse button to  open its window. Now point to the icon that reads "CITY DESK"  and double click the left mouse button. C‚i‚t‚y‚ ‚D‚e‚s‚k‚ will present you with three windows. Now let's get started with an introduction to desktop publishing and typesetting concepts.
